         <cell style="font-size: 11pt;">è la prima e unica lettera. Ehinger vita incredibile: protestante, In 1617 he was called to Augsburg to the Gymnasium St. Anna, where he was appointed rector and librarian of the Gymnasium the following year. But the religious disputes that had already influenced his career soon reappeared. When Ferdinand II's imperial troops captured Augsburg in 1629, the teachers were ordered to renounce the Confessio Augustana by the Counter-Reformation party. Since Ehinger refused, he lost his job and had to flee with his family. At first he found refuge in Protestant areas. On 29 June 1632, Elias Ehinger left Pforte and returned to his former post in Augsburg, which he held until 1635, when the city was once again occupied by imperial troops and the grammar school, including the library, was handed over to the Jesuits.

